  "prompt": "Can a msc chemistry student apply for ISRO summer internship?",
  "response": "Yes, an MSc Chemistry student can apply for a summer internship at the Indian Space Research Organisation (ISRO). ISRO offers various internship opportunities for students from different fields, including science and engineering disciplines. However, the specific eligibility criteria and application process may vary depending on the particular internship program.\n\nTo apply, you should check the official ISRO website or the website of the specific ISRO center you are interested in, as they will provide information on available internships, eligibility requirements, application forms, and deadlines. Additionally, it may be beneficial to have a solid understanding of how your background in chemistry could contribute to ISRO's projects and initiatives.",
